Reasoning: The paper discusses the performance evaluation of numerical algorithms for fluid dynamics problems, which falls under the category of computational science and engineering (cs.CE). The use of finite difference methods for solving these problems suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of numerical analysis (cs.NA). The evaluation of algorithms for future architectures designed to deliver exascale performance suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The use of memory and computational intensity in the evaluation of the algorithms suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of mathematical software (cs.MS). Finally, the focus on algorithmic changes to fully exploit the capabilities of future architectures suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
